Persian Gulf Stocks: Aldar and National Bank of Abu Dhabi

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-06-23T11:14:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/persian-gulf-stocks-aldar-and-national-bank-of-abu-dhabi.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  retreated
0.8 percent to the lowest since May 30, bringing its decline for
the week to 4 percent. Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  declined
0.6 percent. Saudi Arabia’s market is closed for the weekend.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.         Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)   fell to the lowest in
more than three months, dropping 3.7 percent to 1.3 dirhams. The
Abu Dhabi-based real-estate developer had its corporate family
rating and the probability of default rating downgraded by two
notches to B2 from Ba3 at Moody’s Investors Service.        National Bank of Abu Dhabi PJSC (NBAD)   retreated the
most since March 14, falling 2.2 percent to 11.3 dirhams. The
United Arab Emirates’ second-largest lender by assets was cut to
“neutral” from “buy” and had its price estimate raised 4
percent to 13 dirhams at EFG-Hermes Holding SAE.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  